President Obama has nominated Joseph W. Nega and Michael B. Thornton as Judges to the United States Tax Court. Joseph W. Nega is currently a Senior Legislation Counsel to the Joint Committee on Taxation of the United States Congress and has been in this position since 2008. His primary areas of responsibility include individual income tax, tax exemption requirements for state and local bonds, tax credit bonds, and employment taxes. Mr. Nega has been on the Joint Committee staff since 1985. Judge Michael B. Thornton is currently serving as a Judge of the United States Tax Court, a position he has held since March 1998. From June 2012 to March 2013, he served as Chief Judge of the Tax Court. He has previously served in the U.S. Department of the Treasury as Deputy Tax Legislative Counsel and in the U.S. House Committee on Ways and Means. Judge Thornton has a background in law and has received degrees from various universities.